title.narrative: Syria's conflict-affected population have their critical Child Protection needs met, in line with the HRP and as part of the UNICEF JOP.

description.narrative: Escalation of hostilities has severely impacted the physical and psychosocial wellbeing of children. Airstrikes and shelling, and consequent concerns in safety resulted in multiple displacements severely affecting families' capacity to care and protect for their children and resorting to negative coping mechanisms. Implementation experienced delays due to ongoing concerns about safety and security as well as funding constraints. Still, 90% of all child protection interventions took place in high severity locations (4 to 6 severity scale) targeting children and caregivers with the highest needs. The Programme reached total of 247,700 children, parents and caregivers by end of December 2019. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:09/04/2020
